formatted_address: 689578, 21 Choa Chu Kang North 6, B1-49, Singapore
name: Power Cafe

reviews.text: This kind of place deserves our support big time. Bought their nasi padang, cost me $7.20. But a good portion was given.

My favourite go-to place to have nasi lemak in CCK.  The portions are super generous with the rice easily able to feed two hungry persons.  At at $4, it is an unbeatable price.  Hence the long morning and lunch queues.  I noticed that some have complained of the so-called 'bad' service here which I had never experienced.  I kinda think it's reciprocal.  If you're polite, they're polite too :)

The malay auntie wearing white so rude, i told her the money i slot in but never deduct and she have to cheek to ask me THAN follow by AND in a very rude manner?. Common sense, go n check it or do i need to check for you... Food is also getting worst n expensive... They think they talk in Malay i dont understand... And this thing happened 5mins ago

Food is ok. But the service from the skinny Malay auntie really cannot make it. The way she talk to customer is very attitude and a bit rude with her tone. Very impatient and lousy customer service. If I only I could rate lower than 1 star for the service, I will rate -1.

food was really good, unfortunately, their service throws me off. Ordered a few times but their pricing is inconsistent, they really do charge base on their own judgement. Was at the shop in the evening and wasnt sure if they closed, the lady just ignored me and when i walked away, she shouted at me asking what i want while giving a really dull face. It was not just one staff but most times visited with different staffs, they were impolite and disrespectful despite me being polite, which i hope to see an improvement. I would avoid purchasing mainly due to the terrible service.
